 Editor's note: This live event has ended. PRETORIA - The South African Revenue Service says it has collected R1.14-trillion during the 2016/17 fiscal year.#TomMoyane announces #SARS collected R1,144 trillion -in line with revised collection estimate.This is R30billion down from first tax targetCommissioner Tom Moyane announced on Monday the preliminary revenue collection results.Former Finance Minister Pravin Gordhan announced a shortfall of over R30-billion in his budget speech and blamed the revenue service.READ: Moyane accuses Gordhan of interference, wants mediationSARS Commissioner Tom Moyane denied the accusation, blaming the decline on economic factors and a drop in personal income tax due to reductions in wage increases and declines in bonus payouts.eNCA